      "patient_reported_reason": "Annual thyroid review and TSH result",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: 28-year-old female with Hashimoto's thyroiditis on levothyroxine 75 mcg OD since 2022. Reports good energy levels, no palpitations, no weight change. Taking levothyroxine correctly on empty stomach. No constipation or diarrhoea.\n\nObjective: HR 68 bpm, BP 112/70 mmHg, Weight 62 kg. Thyroid not palpably enlarged. No tremor. TSH 1.8 mU/L (normal 0.4–4.0), FT4 14.2 pmol/L (normal 9–19). Anti-TPO antibodies positive (historical).\n\nAssessment: Well-controlled Hashimoto's hypothyroidism on levothyroxine 75 mcg. TSH within therapeutic range.\n\nPlan: Continue levothyroxine 75 mcg OD. Annual TSH monitoring. No dose adjustment required. Advise to avoid taking with calcium, iron, or soy products as these impair absorption.",
